# Pod Count & Rationale for AWS EKS Cluster
# Component          Service Name              Type         Pod Count  Why
# Cluster Autoscaler cluster-autoscaler        Deployment   1          Auto-scale worker nodes
# AWS LB Controller  aws-load-balancer-webhook Deployment   2          High availability for critical ingress management
# ExternalDNS        external-dns               Deployment   1          Sync K8s services to Route53
# Prometheus         prometheus-k8s             Deployment   2          Metrics collection & storage
# Grafana            grafana                    Deployment   1          Single UI, stateless (config in PV)
# Alertmanager       alertmanager-main          Deployment   2          HA for alert routing and deduplication
# Node Exporter      node-exporter              DaemonSet    2          One per node type (per availability zone)
# EBS CSI Controller ebs-csi-controller-svc     Deployment   2          Storage controller HA
# EBS CSI Node       ebs-csi-node               DaemonSet    2          Per-node storage attachment

# CoreDNS            kube-dns                   Deployment   2          HA for cluster DNS resolution
# AWS Node (VPC CNI) vpc-cni-metrics-service    DaemonSet    1          One per worker node across AZs - REQUIRED for pod networking + Assigns AWS VPC IPs to pods + Runs as DaemonSet + Enables security groups for pods
# kube-proxy         kube-proxy                 DaemonSet    1          One per worker node across AZs - REQUIRED for service networking
